<section sectnbr = "1C">
<servcat sctnbr = "01" scnbr = "03">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A1306003" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "03" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Electric Throttle Body Assembly On-Vehicle Inspection
</title>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
If you touch the throttle valve with finger when the ignition is ON and the accelerator pedal is depressed, finger may be pinched in the gap between the throttle valve and throttle body housing if the accelerator pedal is released.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Never touch the throttle valve with finger when the ignition is ON and the accelerator pedal is depressed.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
Failure to take proper precautions when handling the electric throttle body assembly may lead to malfunction of the electric throttle body assembly or damage to its components.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not disassemble the electric throttle body assembly.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not drop or otherwise expose the electric throttle body assembly to large shock. Any electric throttle body assembly that has received large shock should be replaced.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Keep the throttle body housing and/or throttle valve free of dust, metallic particles or other foreign materials.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not apply undue forces to the throttle valve when checking operation of the throttle valve or performance of the TP sensor; otherwise the plastic gears in the throttle valve actuator will be damaged.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention4>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
After replacing electric throttle body assembly, calibration of throttle valve position is required. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1306004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<c-change/>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A1306003001" page = "2">
<title>
Throttle Valve Visual Check
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition OFF.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Remove air cleaner assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Check that there is no foreign material caught between throttle valve and throttle body housing. If foreign materials are present, remove throttle body and clean its inside thoroughly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A1306003002" page = "2">
<title>
Throttle Valve Operation Check
</title>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Set ignition OFF.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Remove air cleaner outlet hose. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check throttle valve operation as follows.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace electric throttle body assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Check that throttle valve (1) moves smoothly to both fully closed position and fully open position when pressed manually.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I8RW0A130001.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "57.506mm" ver = "01" gw = "137" gh = "147"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Check throttle valve returns to default position when finger pressure on throttle valve is released at both fully closed position and fully open position.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Throttle valve default position “a”:
</title>
<ptxt>
6.4&#176; from fully closed position (1)
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A131002.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "43.759mm" ver = "04" gw = "144" gh = "108"/>
</figure>
</spec>
</s2>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<c-change/>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A1306003003" page = "2">
<title>
Electric Throttle Body System Operation Check
</title>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Remove air cleaner outlet hose. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Set ignition ON.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check electric throttle body system as follows.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, go to Step 4).
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Depress accelerator pedal gradually and check that throttle valve moves smoothly until it opens fully.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Release accelerator pedal and check that throttle valve moves back to applicable position.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Throttle valve default position “a”:
</title>
<ptxt>
6.4&#176; from fully closed position (1)
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A131002.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "43.759mm" ver = "04" gw = "144" gh = "108"/>
</figure>
</spec>
</s2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check the following points.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If check results are satisfactory, replace electric throttle body assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Wire harness and connections
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
APP sensor: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1306005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
TP sensor: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1306003005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Throttle motor: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1306003004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
ECM: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1104067"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A1306003004" page = "2">
<title>
Throttle Motor Check
</title>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Set ignition OFF.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Disconnect connector from electric throttle body assembly.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Measure resistance between terminal “1” and terminal “2” of electric throttle body assembly.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace electric throttle body assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Throttle motor resistance
</title>
<ptxt>
0.3 to 100 Ω at 20 &#176;C (68 &#176;F)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAW101130005.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "27.181mm" ver = "01" gw = "93" gh = "61"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A1306003005" page = "2">
<title>
TP Sensor Performance Check
</title>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Set ignition OFF.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Remove air cleaner assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Disconnect connector from electric throttle body assembly.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Check output voltage of TP sensor main and sub signals as follows.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace electric throttle body assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Arrange 3 new 1.5 V batteries (1) in series, and check that total voltage is 4.5 to 5.0 V.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Connect voltmeter (2) and batteries to TP sensor as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAW101130006.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "97.663mm" ver = "01" gw = "152" gh = "260"/>
<callout>
